procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood for laboratory analysis, including pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), hematology, clinical chemistry, serology, HbA1c, pregnancy, and genetic testing.

procedures.name: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.label: Urine Test
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, pregnancy testing, and drug screening.

procedures.name: Insulin Infusion

code.decode: Intravenous infusion, for therapy, prophylaxis, or diagnosis (specify substance or drug); initial, up to 1 hour

procedures.label: Insulin Infusion
procedures.description: Intravenous (IV) insulin infusion to induce hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Nasal Glucagon Administration
procedures.label: Nasal Glucagon Admin
procedures.description: Administration of 3 mg LY900018 (nasal glucagon) for the treatment of insulin-induced hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Intramuscular Glucagon Administration

code.decode: Therapeutic, prophylactic, or diagnostic injection (specify substance or drug); subcutaneous or intramuscular

procedures.label: IM Glucagon Admin
procedures.description: Administration of 1 mg intramuscular glucagon (IMG) for the treatment of insulin-induced hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of supine blood pressure, pulse rate, and body temperature at specified time points.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Recording of single and triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms (ECGs) to monitor cardiac activity.

procedures.name: Bedside Plasma Glucose Monitoring
procedures.label: Bedside PG Monitoring
procedures.description: Frequent monitoring of plasma glucose levels at the bedside for safety during hypoglycemia induction and post-treatment.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A medical physical examination performed at screening.

procedures.name: Height and Weight Measurement
procedures.label: Height and Weight
procedures.description: Measurement of patient's height at screening and weight at specified visits.

procedures.name: Nasal Inspection
procedures.label: Nasal Inspection
procedures.description: Visual inspection of the nasal passages before and after study treatment administration.

procedures.name: Injection-Site Assessment
procedures.label: Injection-Site Assessment
procedures.description: Assessment of the injection site for patients receiving intramuscular glucagon (IMG).

procedures.name: Hypoglycemia Symptom Assessment
procedures.label: Hypoglycemia Questionnaire
procedures.description: Evaluation of recovery from clinical symptoms of hypoglycemia using the Edinburgh Hypoglycemia Scale.

procedures.name: Intravenous Glucose Administration
procedures.label: IV Glucose
procedures.description: Administration of intravenous (IV) glucose if the patient experiences signs and symptoms of severe hypoglycemia requiring intervention.

medicalDevices.name: Nasal Dosing Device
medicalDevices.label: Nasal Glucagon Device
medicalDevices.description: A user-friendly, single-use, nasal dosing device that delivers 3 mg glucagon powder (LY900018).

medicalDevices.name: Syringe and Needle
medicalDevices.label: IM Injection Kit
medicalDevices.description: Device used for intramuscular (IM) injection of reconstituted glucagon powder (GlucaGen).

medicalDevices.name: IV Infusion Pump
medicalDevices.label: IV Pump
medicalDevices.description: Device used for the intravenous (IV) infusion of insulin to induce hypoglycemia.

medicalDevices.name: Bedside Glucose Meter
medicalDevices.label: Glucose Meter
medicalDevices.description: Device for bedside plasma glucose (PG) monitoring for safety.

medicalDevices.name: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform single and triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Continuous Subcutaneous Insulin Infusion Pump
medicalDevices.label: CSII Pump
medicalDevices.description: An insulin pump used by some patients for their daily insulin therapy.
